## Q1: OOH Competitor UI/Brand (Lamar, Outfront, Clear Channel)

**Findings from live sites:**

- **Lamar (lamar.com):** White primary background, dark footer, modern minimalist corporate. Large hero photography, card-based modular sections, generous whitespace. Clean sans-serif throughout.
- **Outfront (outfront.com):** Full dark theme — near-black backgrounds, white text, purple accents. Bold condensed headlines ("WE BUILD BRANDS IN THE REAL WORLD"). High-contrast imagery. Grid-based layout.
- **Clear Channel (clearchanneloutdoor.com):** Corporate B2B aesthetic, large high-contrast imagery, icon-driven stats sections, results-driven framing.

**Industry pattern:** Dark professional theme with bold accent colors is standard for OOH management platforms. Outfront's dark-purple+white is the most modern; Lamar goes lighter/cleaner. Billboard/OOH apps lean into high contrast (mirrors the medium itself).

**Confirmed design system for AdvertEyes** (replace all "preliminary" values in plan.md):

```
Background:        #0A0E1A   (deep navy, darker than Outfront)
Surface/card:      #131929
Card raised:       #1C2540
Border:            #2D3A5A
Accent primary:    #FF6B1A   (billboard orange — high-vis, industry energy)
Accent secondary:  #3B82F6   (DOOH/digital screen blue)
Text primary:      #E8EDF5
Text secondary:    #8A9AC0
Success:           #22C55E
Warning:           #EAB308
Error:             #EF4444

Fonts:
  Display:         Barlow Condensed 700  (OOH industry compressed-headline aesthetic)
  UI/body:         DM Sans 400/500/600   (clean dashboard readability; NOT Inter per CLAUDE.md)
  Monospace/data:  IBM Plex Mono         (KPI figures, route IDs)

Google Fonts import: Barlow+Condensed:wght@700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono
```

Mood: Dark, data-dense, authoritative. Feels like a real ops dashboard for a $50M OOH company. Orange accent echoes the visible, bold nature of the medium.

