## Q3: Open-Meteo Field Names

**Confirmed valid for `/v1/forecast?hourly=...`:**

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `temperature_2m` | Air temp at 2m (°F with `temperature_unit=fahrenheit`) |
| `wind_speed_10m` | Wind speed at 10m above ground |
| `wind_gusts_10m` | Wind gusts (critical for billboard structural safety alerts) |
| `wind_direction_10m` | Wind direction degrees |
| `precipitation` | Total precip sum of preceding hour |
| `weather_code` | WMO numeric weather condition code |
| `visibility` | Viewing distance in meters (directly impacts ad exposure quality) |
| `relative_humidity_2m` | Humidity |
| `apparent_temperature` | "Feels like" temp |

**Sample endpoint:**
```
https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude={lat}&longitude={lon}&hourly=temperature_2m,wind_speed_10m,wind_gusts_10m,precipitation,weather_code,visibility&temperature_unit=fahrenheit&wind_speed_unit=mph&timezone=auto&forecast_days=3
```

No API key required. Completely free. Response field names match exactly as listed. **All plan field names confirmed correct.**

**Added value for OOH context:** `wind_gusts_10m` + `visibility` are operationally relevant (high gusts = billboard safety alerts; low visibility = reduced impression quality). Recommend surfacing these in the asset detail panel.

